HEADWORD: ampere-second
<hw>ampere-second</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a unit of charge
equal to that acquired by the accumulation of one ampere for one
second.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coulomb, C</syn>⟦br⟧
